Data

xeno = readRDS("./Data/10x_xeno_1000.Rds")
suffix = "2Kvargenes"
suffix = r.suffix
import pickle
f = open('./Data/cnmf/cnmf_objects/models_' + suffix + '_cnmf_obj.pckl', 'rb')
cnmf_obj = pickle.load(f)
f.close()

Functionres

library(stringi)
source_from_github(repositoy = "DEG_functions",version = "0.2.1")
source_from_github(repositoy = "cNMF_functions",version = "0.3.1",script_name = "cnmf_function_Harmony.R")
selected_k = 5
suffix = paste(suffix,paste0(selected_k,"nmfK"),sep="_")
print(suffix)
[1] "2Kvargenes_5nmfK"
selected_k = int(r.selected_k)
density_threshold = 0.1
cnmf_obj.consensus(k=selected_k, density_threshold=density_threshold)
usage_norm, gep_scores, gep_tpm, topgenes = cnmf_obj.load_results(K=selected_k, density_threshold=density_threshold)

library(reticulate)
all_metagenes= py$usage_norm


#Make metagene names
for (i in 1:ncol(all_metagenes)) {
  colnames(all_metagenes)[i] = "metagene." %>% paste0(i)
}

#add each metagene to metadata
for (i in 1:ncol(all_metagenes)) {
  metage_metadata = all_metagenes %>% select(i)
  xeno = AddMetaData(object = xeno,metadata = metage_metadata)
}

Programs on UMAP

FeaturePlot(object = xeno,features = colnames(all_metagenes))

Enrichment analysis by top 200 genes of each program

gep_scores = py$gep_scores
plt_list = list()
for (i in 1:ncol(gep_scores)) {
  top_genes = gep_scores  %>%  arrange(desc(gep_scores[i])) #sort by score a
  top = head(rownames(top_genes),200) #take top top_genes_num
  res = genes_vec_enrichment(genes = top,background = rownames(gep_scores),homer = T,title = 
                    i,silent = T,return_all = T)
   
  plt_list[[i]] = res$plt
}
gridExtra::grid.arrange(grobs = plt_list)

Enrichment analysis by selecting genes using “max” method

Enriched in time point

xeno = program_assignment(dataset = xeno,larger_by = 2,program_names = colnames(all_metagenes))
data =FetchData(object = xeno,vars = c("program.assignment","treatment"))
data = data %>% dplyr::count(program.assignment, treatment) %>%  dplyr::add_count(treatment, wt = n, name = "overall")%>% 
mutate(proportion = n / overall)   

plt_list = list()
for (program_name in unique(data$program.assignment)) {
  program_data = data[data$program.assignment == program_name,]
  p = ggplot(data=program_data, aes(x=treatment, y=proportion)) +geom_bar(stat="identity")+ylab("precentage") +ggtitle("program" %>% paste(program_data$program.assignment %>% unique() %>% as.character())) 
    plt_list[[program_name]] = p
}
gridExtra::grid.arrange(grobs = plt_list)


DimPlot(xeno,group.by = "program.assignment",cols = c("red","darkgreen","blue","yellow","black","grey"))
